<define-tag release_date>2000-12-04</define-tag>
#use wml::debian::news

<p>The December 2000 issue of Dr. Dobb's Journal contains an article
entitled 'Inside Debian Hurd' written by Jerry Epplin.  The article is quite
comprehensive and includes a good general overview of why the Hurd exists, a
microkernel architecture overview, and look at the Mach microkernel and Hurd
servers.

<p>The article is available online at:
<div class="center">
   <a href="http://www.ddj.com/articles/2000/0012/0012a/0012a.htm">
   http://www.ddj.com/articles/2000/0012/0012a/0012a.htm</a>
</div>

